To create 4 branches in your Git repository, use these commands (run them one by one in your terminal). I'll assume example names; replace with your preferred names.

git branch branch1 (creates "branch1")
git branch branch2 (creates "branch2")
git branch branch3 (creates "branch3")
git branch branch4 (creates "branch4")
After creating, switch to one with git checkout branch1, or create and switch with git checkout -b newbranch.